Summary

Below are several visualizations describing the customer data for OK All Sports. In general, there are several observations that can be made about past participants that can be helpful for marketing and customer segmentation purposes.

Below are a few graphs and maps which given the opportunity to provide a more in depth review, could yeild valuable insights for the organization.

Sports and Age Participation

The graph below depicts the range of sport participants according to their ages. You may notice that depending on the sport, age groups of participation vary. This information could be helpful for marketing purposes for each sport.

Top Cities by Sport

Below are the top five cities for Archery participants. Events or marketing targeted in areas where Archery enthusiasm is high in proportion to other cities could yeild more participants.

Participants by City

Below a map of Archery look like on a map of Oklahoma cities. This map can also include surrounding states and multiple sports. You may zoom in/out using the plus and minus in the upper left corner. If you click the points more information is available about each city in terms of how many sport participants. The larger the point, the more participants for Archery.

Summary

In summary other analysis methods such as further segmentation by gender and city would be possible with this dataset in addition to expansion of the above analysis, charts, and commentary.
